18
00:00:12,707 --> 00:00:15,707
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,731 --> 00:00:22,818
<i>Jedi-formed rebel alliance
led by Anakin Skywalker!</i>

20
00:00:22,985 --> 00:00:25,071
<i>The Jedi have trained a band of rebels</i>

21
00:00:25,112 --> 00:00:28,449
<i>to fight the Separatists
on the planet Onderon.</i>

22
00:00:28,574 --> 00:00:31,744
<i>With the help of the Jedi,
the rebels escaped capture</i>

23
00:00:31,827 --> 00:00:35,331
<i>and infiltrated
the heavily fortified city of Iziz.</i>

24
00:00:35,456 --> 00:00:37,917
<i>Now our heroes have launched
an armed campaign</i>

25
00:00:37,959 --> 00:00:41,170
<i>to subvert the Separatist occupation
of the planet.</i>

26
00:00:41,295 --> 00:00:44,173
<i>The Jedi Council continue
to observe and advise</i>

27
00:00:44,298 --> 00:00:47,802
<i>as the rebels strive to gain momentum
against the Separatist forces.</i>

28
00:00:48,469 --> 00:00:52,598
<i>Despite the absence of civilian casualties,
public fear has ensued,</i>

29
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:56,936
<i>as reports of the rebels' daring strikes
circulate throughout the city.</i>

30
00:01:09,782 --> 00:01:12,535
-Your identification failed.
-That's not possible.

31
00:01:12,994 --> 00:01:14,328
You are coming with us.

32
00:01:17,164 --> 00:01:19,333
Hey!

33
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:21,669
- What are you doing?
- No!

34
00:01:58,914 --> 00:02:01,042
The rebels are attacking again.

35
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:03,586
That is the fifth time this rotation.

36
00:02:08,424 --> 00:02:11,052
That should give King Rash
something to think about.

37
00:02:11,427 --> 00:02:14,013
I'm sure you've gotten his attention.

38
00:02:30,946 --> 00:02:34,742
Dendup has been summoned
and awaits your order, my lord.

39
00:02:36,911 --> 00:02:38,537
What about the terrorists?

40
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:43,042
They've attacked a checkpoint
near the canal, and two droid patrols.

41
00:02:43,584 --> 00:02:45,252
One in Malgan Market.

42
00:02:45,586 --> 00:02:49,173
If they think destroying a few droids
is going to effect change,

43
00:02:50,049 --> 00:02:51,884
they've run a fool's errand.

44
00:02:51,926 --> 00:02:53,761
One more thing, my lord.

45
00:02:54,512 --> 00:02:59,100
The royal carriage was ambushed
soon after it left the residence.

46
00:02:59,725 --> 00:03:00,851
Hmm.

47
00:03:00,935 --> 00:03:03,104
An attempt on my life?

48
00:03:03,854 --> 00:03:05,272
It appears that way.

49
00:03:08,025 --> 00:03:09,944
Get my predecessor in here.

50
00:03:21,455 --> 00:03:23,374
You surprise me.

51
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:27,628
Engaging with extremists is beneath you.

52
00:03:27,962 --> 00:03:30,881
Do you really want
your crown back that badly?

53
00:03:33,426 --> 00:03:36,303
I only want freedom for my people.

54
00:03:38,723 --> 00:03:41,475
Your supporters are responsible
for terrorist acts

55
00:03:41,559 --> 00:03:43,477
against the kingdom and our allies.

56
00:03:44,311 --> 00:03:46,105
I didn't know that.

57
00:03:46,147 --> 00:03:50,276
You've made it quite impossible
to stay informed of anything

58
00:03:50,317 --> 00:03:52,319
outside my prison chamber.

59
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:55,156
Call off the attacks.

60
00:03:56,490 --> 00:03:59,744
I cannot call off what I did not dictate.

61
00:03:59,827 --> 00:04:03,914
What you are up against
is simply the will of the people.

62
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:08,335
It's up to the king
to embrace, bend or break it.

63
00:04:08,669 --> 00:04:10,588
And I am no longer the king.

64
00:04:11,839 --> 00:04:16,635
Stop the attacks,
or you will atone with your life.

65
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:20,556
It is you that must end the attacks

66
00:04:20,681 --> 00:04:23,642
by ending the droid occupation.

67
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:13,818
Your success will not go unnoticed.

68
00:05:13,901 --> 00:05:15,236
-Yeah !
-All right!

69
00:05:15,402 --> 00:05:16,612
I agree.

70
00:05:16,737 --> 00:05:19,740
But we need to be mindful
of public perception.

71
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:21,826
What was your observation, Padawan?

72
00:05:22,159 --> 00:05:24,662
The people were fearful, Master.

73
00:05:24,745 --> 00:05:25,830
Indeed.

74
00:05:25,913 --> 00:05:27,957
Judging from the reactions I saw today,

75
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:30,918
I'm afraid they will mistake your intentions.

76
00:05:31,335 --> 00:05:32,795
We need to do more damage.

77
00:05:32,878 --> 00:05:36,173
A few dozen broken-down droids
will do little to free Onderon.

78
00:05:36,257 --> 00:05:38,509
The people need to believe
we can succeed.

79
00:05:38,592 --> 00:05:41,053
Without their support,
our efforts are meaningless.

80
00:05:41,303 --> 00:05:43,556
If they're afraid, they won't support us.

81
00:05:43,639 --> 00:05:45,724
We need to assure them of our intentions.

82
00:05:46,058 --> 00:05:48,102
I don't understand. Why are they afraid?

83
00:05:48,185 --> 00:05:50,896
They're afraid
we're not strong enough to win.

84
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:52,773
We need to earn their trust.

85
00:05:53,107 --> 00:05:55,317
You'll have plenty of time
to earn their trust.

86
00:05:55,651 --> 00:05:57,319
All of you are going to be very busy.

87
00:05:58,112 --> 00:06:01,490
Today was only a taste.
You'll get your chance.

88
00:06:03,325 --> 00:06:06,370
In the meantime,
make the most of your victories.

89
00:06:06,453 --> 00:06:08,789
Welcome and learn from them.

90
00:06:09,164 --> 00:06:12,793
Perhaps if we hit something big,
give a show of strength,

91
00:06:13,335 --> 00:06:15,546
they will overcome their fear and join us.

92
00:06:15,796 --> 00:06:17,423
Do you have something in mind?

93
00:06:18,215 --> 00:06:20,217
I know the perfect target.

94
00:06:23,888 --> 00:06:26,307
I think they're ready to give
the 501 some competition.

95
00:06:27,057 --> 00:06:31,186
Let's not get carried away, General.
Though these rebels have impressed me.

96
00:06:31,979 --> 00:06:34,440
We will share the developments
with the Jedi Council.

97
00:06:34,523 --> 00:06:36,859
Ahsoka will remain here as an advisor.

98
00:06:37,234 --> 00:06:39,820
Monitor them
and report back with their progress.

99
00:06:41,113 --> 00:06:44,992
Are you up for it, Snips?
Or would you like to return to Coruscant?

100
00:06:46,201 --> 00:06:49,663
-No, Master. I want to stay.
-Good.

101
00:06:49,872 --> 00:06:51,832
We shall continue to provide
supplies and credits,

102
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:54,335
but they must learn
to operate on their own.

103
00:06:55,127 --> 00:06:57,004
Their survival depends on it.

104
00:06:57,379 --> 00:06:58,923
Yes, Master.

105
00:06:59,256 --> 00:07:01,216
Remember your purpose.

106
00:07:24,531 --> 00:07:27,743
This power generator
feeds substations across the city.

107
00:07:28,744 --> 00:07:31,789
We hit that, the entire grid falls.

108
00:07:31,872 --> 00:07:33,374
How does that help us?

109
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:36,168
Battle droids are no longer
linked to Central Control.

110
00:07:36,251 --> 00:07:37,962
They operate individually.

111
00:07:38,045 --> 00:07:41,131
Yes, but they still need power to recharge.

112
00:07:41,215 --> 00:07:44,385
If we take out this facility,
it will knock out the power grid,

113
00:07:44,468 --> 00:07:45,970
and then it will only be a matter of time

114
00:07:46,053 --> 00:07:49,598
until the droid army
is brought to a standstill, literally.

115
00:07:49,682 --> 00:07:53,602
If you carry the plan out by nightfall,
you'll maximize your strike capability.

116
00:07:54,436 --> 00:07:58,232
Okay, so we just need to figure out
how to destroy the power station.

117
00:07:58,399 --> 00:08:00,150
We need to do more surveillance.

118
00:08:01,485 --> 00:08:03,278
Those droids should have
all the intel we need

119
00:08:03,362 --> 00:08:05,614
stored up in those tin cans of theirs, right?

120
00:08:05,906 --> 00:08:08,242
-They should.
-Then I'll get us one.

121
00:08:31,557 --> 00:08:32,725
Hey, clanker.

122
00:08:37,688 --> 00:08:38,731
Uh-oh.

123
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:52,911
Sentries at every access point,
inside and out.

124
00:08:53,579 --> 00:08:56,040
We can't sustain combat
against their numbers.

125
00:08:56,290 --> 00:09:00,044
But our size makes us perfect
for mobility and surprise.

126
00:09:00,419 --> 00:09:04,381
We need something with heavy firepower
if we are to blow up this facility.

127
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:08,927
If we give them enough trouble,
they'll call for reinforcements.

128
00:09:09,219 --> 00:09:11,388
-Like a tank.
-Exactly.

129
00:09:11,972 --> 00:09:14,141
Then you can provide cover
while we hijack it.

130
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:17,478
And then we use
their own weapon against them.

131
00:09:18,562 --> 00:09:20,647
And bring the droid army to its knees.

132
00:09:32,076 --> 00:09:33,160
Shh.

133
00:09:48,425 --> 00:09:51,345
Remember the plan. We attack this patrol,

134
00:09:51,428 --> 00:09:53,514
and hopefully they will
call in a tank for backup.

135
00:10:17,871 --> 00:10:19,498
Let's go!

136
00:10:31,677 --> 00:10:33,512
Patrol 118 to Central.

137
00:10:35,722 --> 00:10:39,017
We've been ambushed by terrorists
and need reinforcements.

138
00:10:40,561 --> 00:10:42,354
Let's hope they send a tank.

139
00:10:45,357 --> 00:10:47,609
Hear that? They sent destroyers.

140
00:10:47,734 --> 00:10:48,735
Move!

141
00:11:05,419 --> 00:11:07,921
We're not gonna last
unless we take out those destroyers.

142
00:11:08,088 --> 00:11:10,299
-We have to get behind them.
-Let's go.

143
00:11:32,988 --> 00:11:34,656
Roll it slow so it gets through.

144
00:11:34,823 --> 00:11:35,949
I know that.

145
00:11:37,951 --> 00:11:40,120
-Nice job!
-You screwed me up!

146
00:11:59,973 --> 00:12:01,350
Thanks.

147
00:12:04,186 --> 00:12:06,980
I've never seen a destroyer
taken out that way before.

148
00:12:07,105 --> 00:12:08,273
We all have to adapt.

149
00:12:13,612 --> 00:12:14,947
There's our tank.

150
00:12:17,824 --> 00:12:19,326
Split up!

151
00:12:48,689 --> 00:12:50,023
Let's move.

152
00:13:23,432 --> 00:13:26,393
Good work. Now let's get this thing
up and running again.

153
00:13:41,199 --> 00:13:42,534
What are you waiting for?

154
00:13:42,576 --> 00:13:43,910
Give me a second.

155
00:13:44,244 --> 00:13:47,205
-Do you know what you're doing?
-Yeah, I know what I'm doing.

156
00:13:49,249 --> 00:13:50,584
You boys having a problem?

157
00:13:50,792 --> 00:13:52,878
No. No problem. Why?

158
00:13:52,919 --> 00:13:54,921
Well, come on, we need to get moving.

159
00:13:55,422 --> 00:13:56,757
Hey, who put you in charge?

160
00:13:57,049 --> 00:13:59,718
All right, get out of the tank, hot shot.

161
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,470
This needs a woman's touch.

162
00:14:01,928 --> 00:14:03,722
Fine, be my guest.

163
00:14:04,097 --> 00:14:05,807
We need to get to that power generator

164
00:14:05,932 --> 00:14:07,934
before they realize
this tank's gone missing.

165
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:09,603
We're running out of time.

166
00:14:11,605 --> 00:14:12,773
I was gonna do that.

167
00:14:13,106 --> 00:14:14,149
Uh-huh.

168
00:14:14,274 --> 00:14:15,817
Sure.

169
00:14:19,196 --> 00:14:20,781
Couldn't have done it better myself.

170
00:14:21,782 --> 00:14:23,158
Now that's the truth.

171
00:14:46,681 --> 00:14:48,725
I'll draw their fire. Good luck.

172
00:14:48,809 --> 00:14:50,018
Good luck.

173
00:14:50,477 --> 00:14:51,686
I'll cover you.

174
00:15:14,251 --> 00:15:17,045
We're almost in position.
Ready when you are, Steela.

175
00:15:21,508 --> 00:15:23,051
A sniper! Get her!

176
00:15:23,885 --> 00:15:25,220
Roger, roger.

177
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:52,414
Look, we have reinforcements.

178
00:15:54,458 --> 00:15:56,918
Hey, you're not a droid !
Get down from there!

179
00:16:17,606 --> 00:16:18,773
Fire the gun!

180
00:16:19,232 --> 00:16:20,609
This gun is recharging!

181
00:16:31,119 --> 00:16:32,245
You're all clear.

182
00:16:55,352 --> 00:16:57,604
Looks like all that training is paying off.

183
00:17:04,194 --> 00:17:08,532
My lord, without power,
the droids will be massacred.

184
00:17:09,324 --> 00:17:12,661
This loss will work for us.

185
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:28,760
There's been a power outage.

186
00:17:28,843 --> 00:17:30,804
I've lost contact with Command.

187
00:17:30,887 --> 00:17:32,514
Switch to infrared.

188
00:17:38,144 --> 00:17:39,729
-It's the rebels!
-Fight for Onderon!

189
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:41,314
-They're destroying the droids!
-Free Onderon!

190
00:17:41,398 --> 00:17:44,859
- Freedom !
- Fight for freedom!

191
00:17:45,151 --> 00:17:47,320
- Free Onderon !
- Freedom ! Freedom!

192
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:02,502
- For freedom !
- For Onderon!

193
00:18:09,009 --> 00:18:12,387
- Yes!
- Freedom for Onderon!

194
00:18:22,647 --> 00:18:25,400
-We must celebrate.
-With pleasure.

195
00:18:25,483 --> 00:18:27,944
- Did you see that?
- I knew we could do it!

196
00:18:30,488 --> 00:18:32,782
Come here, you handsome senator.

197
00:18:38,788 --> 00:18:42,042
<i>-Steela is a born leader.
-And quite courageous, I hear.</i>

198
00:18:45,086 --> 00:18:48,214
<i>Ahsoka, remember what I told you
about staying focused.</i>

199
00:18:48,715 --> 00:18:50,508
I can't help it, Master.

200
00:18:50,634 --> 00:18:53,011
<i>-I understand.</i>
-You do?

201
00:18:53,094 --> 00:18:57,557
<i>I do. But try to remember,
always put purpose ahead of your feelings.</i>

202
00:18:58,308 --> 00:19:02,020
<i>This latest development will surely
get Count Dooku's attention.</i>

203
00:19:02,103 --> 00:19:04,356
<i>He will respond harshly.</i>

204
00:19:04,439 --> 00:19:06,483
<i>They will stop at nothing to find you.</i>

205
00:19:06,566 --> 00:19:09,194
<i>You must adapt
and continue to confront them</i>

206
00:19:09,277 --> 00:19:10,612
<i>in order to liberate Onderon.</i>

207
00:19:10,695 --> 00:19:12,989
-We will.
-And we shall win.

208
00:19:13,198 --> 00:19:15,283
<i>In that, I have no doubt.</i>

209
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:18,745
<i>Now you must rally the people.
You will need their support.</i>

210
00:19:19,913 --> 00:19:24,501
<i>Your ability to influence them will also
determine your capacity to represent them,</i>

211
00:19:24,918 --> 00:19:26,961
<i>not only on the battlefield, but off of it.</i>

212
00:19:27,045 --> 00:19:29,756
<i>Against your enemies,
even within your own ranks.</i>

213
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:32,550
<i>Your commitment will inspire others.</i>

214
00:19:32,842 --> 00:19:35,136
<i>Your conviction will lead to victory.</i>

215
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:38,014
<i>After tonight's efforts,
the people will be ready to follow.</i>

216
00:19:38,473 --> 00:19:40,975
<i>You will need a leader
for them to rally behind.</i>

217
00:19:44,729 --> 00:19:47,107
They are waging a very public war.

218
00:19:49,109 --> 00:19:51,069
Every trespass is an embarrassment.

219
00:19:52,404 --> 00:19:56,658
<i>Your forces cannot manage
a small band of terrorists?</i>

220
00:19:56,950 --> 00:20:00,370
My lord, your droids
have become ineffective

221
00:20:00,453 --> 00:20:02,288
against the mounting rebel attacks.

222
00:20:02,580 --> 00:20:05,667
<i>I thought I could trust you to rule Onderon.</i>

223
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:09,254
<i>I find this report most disappointing.</i>

224
00:20:12,298 --> 00:20:17,053
It seems that the rebels are far more
organized than they were in the past.

225
00:20:17,262 --> 00:20:19,806
The attack against
the power generators proves that.

226
00:20:20,473 --> 00:20:24,811
Perhaps it's time you sent me better
reinforcements than the droids I have.

227
00:20:25,103 --> 00:20:27,522
<i>I will grant you this request,</i>

228
00:20:27,605 --> 00:20:31,776
<i>and not only send you better droids
but a better general.</i>

229
00:20:32,193 --> 00:20:37,574
<i>This is Kalani. I assure you
he will succeed where you have failed.</i>

230
00:20:41,703 --> 00:20:43,830
We need to build on our momentum

231
00:20:44,038 --> 00:20:46,750
and continue our attacks
to keep them off balance.

232
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:49,294
We have to assure the people first.

233
00:20:49,377 --> 00:20:52,714
If we keep disrupting their lives,
we risk alienating them.

234
00:20:52,839 --> 00:20:55,008
We have to gain their trust.

235
00:20:55,341 --> 00:20:58,678
I agree with both of you.
We can balance both.

236
00:20:58,762 --> 00:21:01,556
We also need to recruit others to join us.

237
00:21:02,265 --> 00:21:03,808
Onderon is ours.

238
00:21:03,892 --> 00:21:07,103
We will remind everyone,
and keep reminding them,

239
00:21:07,187 --> 00:21:08,813
until we get it back.

240
00:21:08,897 --> 00:21:11,983
- Onderon is ours!
- Free Onderon!

241
00:21:12,525 --> 00:21:15,028
-For freedom !
-Onderon is ours!

242
00:21:18,239 --> 00:21:20,742
All in favor of Steela as our leader,

243
00:21:21,659 --> 00:21:23,077
raise your hand.

244
00:21:26,998 --> 00:21:29,876
Okay, looks like it's been decided.

245
00:21:30,376 --> 00:21:32,003
You're the leader.

246
00:21:33,463 --> 00:21:35,048
Saw...

247
00:21:35,298 --> 00:21:37,550
Let him go.
He just needs to blow off some steam.

248
00:21:37,634 --> 00:21:38,718
He'll be back.

249
00:21:40,345 --> 00:21:41,554
I can't.

250
00:21:42,555 --> 00:21:43,723
Why?

251
00:21:44,516 --> 00:21:45,892
